# Turnkey API Integration Rules for Cursor

## Documentation Sources
- Full API Reference: docs/turnkey/llms-full.txt
- Concise Reference: docs/turnkey/llms.txt
- Online Documentation: https://docs.turnkey.com/llms-full.txt

## Key API Endpoints
- POST /public/v1/submit/approve_activity - Approve an activity
- POST /public/v1/submit/create_api_keys - Create API keys for a user
- POST /public/v1/submit/sign_transaction - Sign a transaction
- POST /public/v1/submit/create_authenticators - Create authenticators

## Authentication Requirements
- All requests require X-Stamp header with cryptographically signed request
- Organization ID is required for all endpoints
- API keypair (public/private) needed for signing requests

## Common Request Structure
```json
{
  "type": "ACTIVITY_TYPE_*",
  "timestampMs": "timestamp_in_milliseconds",
  "organizationId": "your_organization_id",
  "parameters": {
    // endpoint-specific parameters
  }
}
```

## Activity Types
- ACTIVITY_TYPE_APPROVE_ACTIVITY
- ACTIVITY_TYPE_CREATE_API_KEYS_V2
- ACTIVITY_TYPE_SIGN_TRANSACTION_V2
- ACTIVITY_TYPE_CREATE_AUTHENTICATORS

## When working with Turnkey API:
1. Always include proper authentication headers
2. Use correct activity types
3. Include timestamp in milliseconds
4. Reference the full documentation for specific endpoint details
5. Handle responses according to Turnkey's response format
